## Additional Cognitive and Behavioral Symptoms Related to Long-Term Trauma

Beyond the core cognitive domains, trauma exposure can also manifest in behavioral and emotional symptoms that indirectly affect cognition:

| Symptom                         | Description                                                                                     |
|--------------------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Problems with physical coordination | Motor difficulties potentially linked to trauma-related neurological changes ([Quirke, n.d.](https://michaelgquirke.com/what-are-the-cognitive-effects-of-trauma-on-the-brain/)) |
| Self-isolation and withdrawal  | Social disengagement that may exacerbate cognitive decline through reduced cognitive stimulation ([FHE Rehab, n.d.](https://fherehab.com/trauma/signs-symptoms)) |
| Difficulty setting boundaries  | Impaired judgment and executive control impacting interpersonal relationships ([Quirke, n.d.](https://michaelgquirke.com/what-are-the-cognitive-effects-of-trauma-on-the-brain/)) |
| Dysfunctional emotional regulation | Mood instability and impulsivity linked to executive dysfunction ([Quirke, n.d.](https://michaelgquirke.com/what-are-the-cognitive-effects-of-trauma-on-the-brain/)) |
| Shame, guilt, and low self-esteem | Emotional states that can interfere with cognitive engagement and motivation ([FHE Rehab, n.d.](https://fherehab.com/trauma/signs-symptoms)) |
| Poor impulse control and aggressive behavior | Behavioral manifestations of impaired executive function ([Quirke, n.d.](https://michaelgquirke.com/what-are-the-cognitive-effects-of-trauma-on-the-brain/)) |
| Sleeping and eating disturbances | Disruptions that negatively affect cognitive performance and memory consolidation ([FHE Rehab, n.d.](https://fherehab.com/trauma/signs-symptoms)) |

These symptoms can create a feedback loop, worsening cognitive impairments and complicating recovery.

